In [ ]:
def get_de_error(gt_bbox, pred_bbox, filter_boundry = 100):
    if len(gt_bbox) > 1 or len(pred_bbox) > 1:
        raise ValueError("Only one bounding box is expected")
    gt_exists = len(gt_bbox) != 0
    pred_exists = len(pred_bbox) != 0
    if gt_exists and pred_exists: # True Positive
        gt_dist = gt_bbox[0].center[1]
        pred_dist = pred_bbox[0].center[1]
    elif not gt_exists and not pred_exists: # True Negative
        gt_dist = filter_boundry
        pred_dist = filter_boundry
    elif not gt_exists and pred_exists: # False Positive
        gt_dist = filter_boundry
        pred_dist = pred_bbox[0].center[1]
    elif gt_exists and not pred_exists: # False Negative
        gt_dist = gt_bbox[0].center[1]
        pred_dist = filter_boundry
    return gt_dist, pred_dist, gt_exists, pred_exists

# Load results
results = pickle.load(open('result_list.pkl','rb'))
# token, gt_lead, pred_lead
print(results[0].keys())
data ={
    'token':[],
    'gt_dist':[],
    'pred_dist':[],
    'gt_exist':[],
    'pred_exist':[],
}
for res_dict in results:
    gt_dist, pred_dist, gt_exist, pred_exist = get_de_error(res_dict['gt_lead'], res_dict['pred_lead'])
    data['token'].append(res_dict['token'])
    data['gt_dist'].append(gt_dist)
    data['pred_dist'].append(pred_dist)
    data['gt_exist'].append(gt_exist)
    data['pred_exist'].append(pred_exist)
data['token'] = np.array(data['token'])
data['gt_dist'] = np.array(data['gt_dist'])
data['pred_dist'] = np.array(data['pred_dist'])
data['gt_exist'] = np.array(data['gt_exist'])
data['pred_exist'] = np.array(data['pred_exist'])

In [ ]:
def get_confusion_matrix(data):
      sample_tokens = data['token']
      dist_error = data['gt_dist']-data['pred_dist']

      false_positive = np.logical_and(~data['gt_exist'], data['pred_exist'])
      false_negative = np.logical_and(data['gt_exist'], ~data['pred_exist'])
      true_negative = np.logical_and(~data['gt_exist'], ~data['pred_exist'])
      true_positive = np.logical_and(data['gt_exist'], data['pred_exist'])
      tp_samples = sample_tokens[true_positive]
      tp_dist_error = dist_error[true_positive]#
      tp_dist = data['gt_dist'][true_positive]
      n_samples = len(true_positive)
      n_tp = np.sum(true_positive)
      n_fp = np.sum(false_positive)
      n_tn = np.sum(true_negative)
      n_fn = np.sum(false_negative)
      print(f'Total Samples: {n_samples},\n \
      True Positive: {n_tp} ({n_tp/n_samples*100:.2f}%),\n \
      False Positive: {n_fp} ({n_fp/n_samples*100:.2f}%),\n \
      True Negative: {n_tn} ({n_tn/n_samples*100:.2f}%),\n \
      False Negative: {n_fn} ({n_fn/n_samples*100:.2f}%)'
            )
      print('TP only: Mean Longitudinal Distance Error: {}, Median Longitudinal Distance Error: {}'.format(np.mean(tp_dist_error), np.median(tp_dist_error)))
      return {
          'TP': true_positive,
          'FP': false_positive,
          'TN': true_negative,
          'FN': false_negative,
          'DE': tp_dist_error,
          'TP_dist': tp_dist
      }

# plot ecdf using plotly scatter
import plotly.express as px
import plotly.graph_objects as go
import plotly.io as pio
from plotly.offline import init_notebook_mode
from plotly.subplots import make_subplots

init_notebook_mode(connected=True)

def plot_ecdf(fig, data, title):
    n_samples = len(data)
    x = np.sort(data)
    y = np.arange(1, n_samples+1)/n_samples
    fig.add_trace(go.Scatter(x=x, y=y, mode='lines', name=title))
    return fig

fig = go.Figure()
fig = plot_ecdf(fig, np.abs(confusion_matrix['DE']), 'All')
fig = plot_ecdf(fig, np.abs(rainy_confusion_matrix['DE']), 'Rainy')
fig = plot_ecdf(fig, np.abs(non_rainy_confusion_matrix['DE']), 'Non Rainy')
fig.update_layout(title='Absolute Longitudinal Distance Error ECDF', xaxis_title='Longitudinal Distance Error(m)', yaxis_title='ECDF')

fig.show()
